1. General DO-178C Code Commenting Rules
In your Java code, every class, method, and important logic must be documented.
The rule is simple:
Code Element	Comment Requirement
Class	Purpose of the class, author, date, version
Method	Purpose, parameters, return value, exceptions
Complex Logic	Inline explanation if necessary
Database Access	What queries are executed and why